@ENDNODE

@NODE "Word_Right" "Word_Right"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Word_Right

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Move the Cursor to the start of the next word.

 See Also   : @{"Word_Left" Link "Word_Left"} @{"Word_End" Link "Word_End"} @{"Word_Delete" Link "Word_Delete"} @{"Complete_Word" Link "Complete_Word"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Word_End" "Word_End"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Word_End

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Move the Cursor to the end of the current word.

 See Also   : @{"Word_Left" Link "Word_Left"} @{"Word_Right" Link "Word_Right"} @{"Word_Delete" Link "Word_Delete"} @{"Complete_Word" Link "Complete_Word"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Goto_Line" "Goto_Line"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Goto_Line

 PARAMETERS : LINE/N

 DESCRIPTION: Goto a line Number.  If Line number is not given then display a
              Requester asking for a line number.

 See Also   : @{"Goto_Column" Link "Goto_Column"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Goto_Column" "Goto_Column"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Goto_Column

 PARAMETERS : COLUMN/N/A

 DESCRIPTION: Goto the Column Number given.

 See Also   : @{"Goto_Line" Link "Goto_Line"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Next_Buffer" "Next_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Next_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Switch to the next buffer in the list.

 See Also   : @{"Prev_Buffer" Link "Prev_Buffer"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"} @{"Kill_Buffer" Link "Kill_Buffer"} @{"Make_Buffer" Link "Make_Buffer"} @{"Print_Buffer" Link "Print_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Prev_Buffer" "Prev_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Prev_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Switch to the previous buffer in the list.

 See Also   : @{"Next_Buffer" Link "Next_Buffer"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"} @{"Kill_Buffer" Link "Kill_Buffer"} @{"Make_Buffer" Link "Make_Buffer"} @{"Print_Buffer" Link "Print_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Goto_Buffer" "Goto_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Goto_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : BUFFER

 DESCRIPTION: Switch to the buffer given.  If NO buffer given then show a
              requester listing all buffers and select a buffer to switch to.

 See Also   : @{"Next_Buffer" Link "Next_Buffer"} @{"Prev_Buffer" Link "Prev_Buffer"} @{"Kill_Buffer" Link "Kill_Buffer"} @{"Make_Buffer" Link "Make_Buffer"} @{"Print_Buffer" Link "Print_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Next_Fold" "Next_Fold"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Next_Fold

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Move to the Next Fold if any.

 See Also   : @{"Fold_Line" Link "Fold_Line"} @{"Unfold" Link "Unfold"} @{"Prev_Fold" Link "Prev_Fold"} @{"Fold_Block" Link "Fold_Block"} @{"Unfold_Line" Link "Unfold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Prev_Fold" "Prev_Fold"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Prev_Fold

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Move to the Previous Fold if any.

 See Also   : @{"Fold_Line" Link "Fold_Line"} @{"Unfold" Link "Unfold"} @{"Next_Fold" Link "Next_Mark"} @{"Fold_Block" Link "Fold_Block"} @{"Unfold_Line" Link "Unfold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Next_Mark" "Next_Mark"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Next_Mark

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Make the Next Mark the Current Mark.

 See Also   : @{"Mark" Link "Mark"} @{"Unmark" Link "Unmark"} @{"Prev_Mark" Link "Prev_Mark"} @{"Goto_Mark" Link "Goto_Mark"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Prev_Mark" "Prev_Mark"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Prev_Mark

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Make the previous Mark the Current Mark.

 See Also   : @{"Mark" Link "Mark"} @{"Unmark" Link "Unmark"} @{"Next_Mark" Link "Next_Mark"} @{"Goto_Mark" Link "Goto_Mark"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Goto_Mark" "Goto_Mark"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Goto_Mark

 PARAMETERS : MARKNUM/N

 DESCRIPTION: If no parameter then
                 move to the current Mark
              else
                 move to mark number NUM.

 See Also   : @{"Mark" Link "Mark"} @{"Unmark" Link "Unmark"} @{"Next_Mark" Link "Next_Mark"} @{"Prev_Mark" Link "Prev_Mark"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Match" "Match"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Match

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Currently matches up {([ & ])}

 See Also   : @{"Count_Braces" Link "Count_Braces"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Return" "Return"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Return

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Splits the line at the Cursor position.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Backspace" "Backspace"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Backspace

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Deletes the character to the left of the Cursor.  If the
              Cursor is at the start of the line then Join the current line
              to the line above.

 See Also   : @{"Del" Link "Del"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Del" "Del"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Del

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Deletes the character under the Cursor.  If the Cursor is at
              the end of the line the join the line below to the current
              line.

 See Also   : @{"Backspace" Link "Backspace"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Del_Line" "Del_Line"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Del_Line

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Delete the current line.

 See Also   : @{"Del_EOL" Link "Del_EOL"} @{"Del_SOL" Link "Del_SOL"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Word_Delete" "Word_Delete"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Word_Delete

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Delete the Word beneath the Cursor.

 See Also   : @{"Word_Left" Link "Word_Left"} @{"Word_Right" Link "Word_Right"} @{"Word_End" Link "Word_End"} @{"Complete_Word" Link "Complete_Word"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Del_EOL" "Del_EOL"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Del_EOL

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Delete all characters from Cursor until the End Of Line.

 See Also   : @{"Del_Line" Link "Del_Line"} @{"Del_SOL" Link "Del_SOL"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Del_SOL" "Del_SOL"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Del_SOL

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Delete all characters from Cursor until the Start Of Line.

 See Also   : @{"Del_EOL" Link "Del_EOL"} @{"Del_Line" Link "Del_Line"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Begin" "Block_Begin"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Begin

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Set the Start of a block to the Cursor position.

 See Also   : @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_End" "Block_End"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_End

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Set the End of a block to the Cursor position.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Copy" "Block_Copy"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Copy

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Copy a Block to the Cursor position.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Delete" "Block_Delete"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Delete

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Delete the current Block.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Move" "Block_Move"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Move

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Move the current block to the Cursor position.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Hide" "Block_Hide"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Hide

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Turn off the block.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Clip" "Block_Clip"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Clip

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Copy the Current block to the clipboard Unit 0

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Clip_Block" "Clip_Block"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Clip_Block

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Copy the contents of Clipboard Unit 0 to the Buffer and make
              it the current block.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_File" "Block_File"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_File

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Copy the current block to a File.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "File_Block" "File_Block"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : File_Block

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Copy a file into the current buffer and make it the current
              block.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Block_Mode" "Block_Mode"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Block_Mode

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Switch between Normal Block Mode and Column Block Mode.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Indent_Block" "Indent_Block"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Indent_Block

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Inserts 1 space before each fully highlighted line.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unindent_Block" "Unindent_Block"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Unindent_Block

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Removes 1 space before each fully highlighted line.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Undo" Link "Undo"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Undo" "Undo"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Undo

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Reverses the effects of Block_Delete, Del_Line & Word_Delete.
              The Undo limit is set by MAXUNDO.

 See Also   : @{"Block_Begin" Link "Block_Begin"} @{"Block_End" Link "Block_End"} @{"Block_Copy" Link "Block_Copy"} @{"Block_Delete" Link "Block_Delete"} @{"Block_Move" Link "Block_Move"}
              @{"Block_Hide" Link "Block_Hide"} @{"Block_Mode" Link "Block_Mode"} @{"Block_Clip" Link "Block_Clip"} @{"Clip_Block" Link "Clip_Block"} @{"Block_File" Link "Block_File"}
              @{"File_Block" Link "File_Block"} @{"Indent_Block" Link "Indent_Block"} @{"Unindent_Block" Link "Unindent_Block"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Split_Window" "Split_Window"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Split_Window

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Split the current window into 2 windows.

 See Also   : @{"Close_Window" Link "Close_Window"} @{"Zoom" Link "Zoom"} @{"Explode" Link "Explode"} @{"Refresh" Link "Refresh"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Close_Window" "Close_Window"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Close_Window

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Close the current window.

 See Also   : @{"Split_Window" Link "Split_Window"} @{"Zoom" Link "Zoom"} @{"Explode" Link "Explode"} @{"Refresh" Link "Refresh"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Zoom" "Zoom"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Zoom

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Switch between Full sized window and current size of window.

 See Also   : @{"Split_Window" Link "Split_Window"} @{"Close_Window" Link "Close_Window"} @{"Explode" Link "Explode"} @{"Refresh" Link "Refresh"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Explode" "Explode"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Explode

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Make the current window full size.

 See Also   : @{"Split_Window" Link "Split_Window"} @{"Close_Window" Link "Close_Window"} @{"Zoom" Link "Zoom"} @{"Refresh" Link "Refresh"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Refresh" "Refresh"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Refresh

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Force a refresh of all windows.

 See Also   : @{"Split_Window" Link "Split_Window"} @{"Close_Window" Link "Close_Window"} @{"Zoom" Link "Zoom"} @{"Explode" Link "Explode"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Load_File" "Load_File"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Load_File

 PARAMETERS : NAME,OVER/S,NODUP/S

 DESCRIPTION: Load a file into a Buffer.

              NAME  : The name of the file to load - Full path preferred.
                      If not present then get a filename from the filerequester.
              OVER  : If present the current buffer will be OVERWRITTEN.
              NODUP : If present the Buffer list will be searched and if the file
                      requested is already in memory then the file will not be
                      loaded.

 See Also   : @{"Save_File" Link "Save_File"} @{"Print_File" Link "Print_File"} @{"Reload" Link "Reload"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Save_File" "Save_File"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Save_File

 PARAMETERS : NEW/S

 DESCRIPTION: Save the current buffer.  If the file is a temp file or parameter NEW
              present then request a new filename.

 See Also   : @{"Load_File" Link "Load_File"} @{"Print_File" Link "Print_Buffer"} @{"Reload" Link "Reload"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Print_File" "Print_File"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Print_File

 PARAMETERS : NAME

 DESCRIPTION: Print the given file.  If no file given then prompt for a filename.
              Printing is accomplished by executing the PRINTER string with the
              filename appended.

 See Also   : @{"Load_File" Link "Load_File"} @{"Save_File" Link "Save_File"} @{"Reload" Link "Reload"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Reload" "Reload"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Reload

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Read the Reload file (Skoed.Memory) and load all files
              contained in it.

 See Also   : @{"Load_File" Link "Load_File"} @{"Save_File" Link "Save_File"} @{"Print_File" Link "Print_File"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Kill_Buffer" "Kill_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Kill_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Free the current Buffer.

 See Also   : @{"Next_Buffer" Link "Next_Buffer"} @{"Prev_Buffer" Link "Prev_Buffer"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"} @{"Make_Buffer" Link "Make_Buffer"} @{"Print_Buffer" Link "Print_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Make_Buffer" "Make_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Make_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Create a new buffer named "Temp". Please note temp files are
              not saved and are not put into memory files.

 See Also   : @{"Next_Buffer" Link "Next_Buffer"} @{"Prev_Buffer" Link "Prev_Buffer"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"} @{"Kill_Buffer" Link "Kill_Buffer"} @{"Print_Buffer" Link "Print_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Print_Buffer" "Print_Buffer"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Print_Buffer

 PARAMETERS : BUFFER

 DESCRIPTION: Print the buffer specified. If no buffer specified then select a
              buffer from the list.  Printing is accomplished by saveing the buffer
              to C_DIR and then append the filename to the PRINTER string before
              executeing the PRINTER string.

 See Also   : @{"Next_Buffer" Link "Next_Buffer"} @{"Prev_Buffer" Link "Prev_Buffer"} @{"Goto_Buffer" Link "Goto_Buffer"} @{"Kill_Buffer" Link "Kill_Buffer"} @{"Make_Buffer" Link "Make_Buffer"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Compile" "Compile"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Compile

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Save the current file to C_DIR, Append the filename to the
              compile string and then Execute it.

 See Also   : @{"Link" Link "Link"} @{"Make" Link "Make"} @{"Run" Link "Run"} @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} @{"New_CLI" Link "New_CLI"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Link" "Link"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Link

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Execute the LINK string.

 See Also   : @{"Compile" Link "Compile"} @{"Make" Link "Make"} @{"Run" Link "Run"} @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} @{"New_CLI" Link "New_CLI"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Run" "Run"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Run

 PARAMETERS : COMMAND

 DESCRIPTION: Execute the given command or (if no command given) display a 
              requester asking for a EXECUTE string and then execute it.

 See Also   : @{"Compile" Link "Compile"} @{"Make" Link "Make"} @{"Link" Link "Link"} @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} @{"New_CLI" Link "New_CLI"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Make" "Make"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Make

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Execute the MAKE string.

 See Also   : @{"Compile" Link "Compile"} @{"Link" Link "Link"} @{"Run" Link "Run"} @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} @{"New_CLI" Link "New_CLI"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Errors" "Errors"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Errors

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Execute the ERRORS string.

 See Also   : @{"Compile" Link "Compile"} @{"Make" Link "Make"} @{"Run" Link "Run"} @{"Link" Link "Link"} @{"New_CLI" Link "New_CLI"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "New_CLI" "New_CLI"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : New_CLI

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Execute the NEWCLI string.

 See Also   : @{"Compile" Link "Compile"} @{"Make" Link "Make"} @{"Run" Link "Run"} @{"Errors" Link "Errors"} @{"Link" Link "Link"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Find" "Find"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Find

 PARAMETERS : FIND,CONT/S,NOCASE/S,ALLBUF/S

 DESCRIPTION: Find a String.
              The following options are available :
                  No Care Case : Case is ignored in search.    (NOCASE)
                  All Buffers  : Search all buffers for word.  (ALLBUF)
                  Continuous   : Count words instead of search.(CONT)
                                 (Not yet implemented)

 See Also   : @{"Replace" Link "Replace"} @{"Again" Link "Again"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Replace" "Replace"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Replace

 PARAMETERS : FIND,REPLACE,CONT/S,NOCASE/S,ALLBUF/S,QUERY/S

 DESCRIPTION: Find and Replace a string.
              The following options are available :
                  No Care Case : Case is ignored in search.   (NOCASE)
                  All Buffers  : Search all buffers for word. (ALLBUF)
                  Continuous   : Replace all words.           (CONT)
                  Query        : Ask before replacing.        (QUERY)

 See Also   : @{"Find" Link "Find"} @{"Again" Link "Again"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Again" "Again"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Again

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Repeat previous Find or Replace command

 See Also   : @{"Find" Link "Find"} @{"Replace" Link "Replace"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Mark" "Mark"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Mark

 PARAMETERS : MARKNUM/N

 DESCRIPTION: Create a new mark at current position.
              An optional Number may be given as a parameter and will be assigned to
              this mark.  Parameter must be > 0.

 See Also   : @{"Unmark" Link "Unmark"} @{"Next_Mark" Link "Next_Mark"} @{"Prev_Mark" Link "Prev_Mark"} @{"Goto_Mark" Link "Goto_Mark"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unmark" "Unmark"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Unmark

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Remove the current Mark.

 See Also   : @{"Mark" Link "Mark"} @{"Next_Mark" Link "Next_Mark"} @{"Prev_Mark" Link "Prev_Mark"} @{"Goto_Mark" Link "Goto_Mark"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Fold_Line" "Fold_Line"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Fold_Line

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Fold the current line.

 See Also   : @{"Unfold" Link "Unfold"} @{"Next_Fold" Link "Next_Fold"} @{"Prev_Fold" Link "Prev_Fold"} @{"Fold_Block" Link "Fold_Block"} @{"Unfold_Line" Link "Unfold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unfold_Line" "Unfold_Line"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Unfold_Line

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Unfold a line from a fold

 See Also   : @{"Unfold" Link "Unfold"} @{"Next_Fold" Link "Next_Fold"} @{"Prev_Fold" Link "Prev_Fold"} @{"Fold_Block" Link "Fold_Block"} @{"Fold_Line" Link "Fold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Fold_Block" "Fold_Block"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Fold_Block

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Fold an entire block

 See Also   : @{"Unfold" Link "Unfold"} @{"Next_Fold" Link "Next_Fold"} @{"Prev_Fold" Link "Prev_Fold"} @{"Fold_Line" Link "Fold_Line"} @{"Unfold_Line" Link "Unfold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Unfold" "Unfold"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Unfold

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Unfold the entire fold

 See Also   : @{"Next_Fold" Link "Next_Fold"} @{"Prev_Fold" Link "Prev_Fold"} @{"Fold_Block" Link "Fold_Block"} @{"Unfold_Line" Link "Unfold_Line"} @{"Fold_Line" Link "Fold_Line"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Str_Size" "Str_Size"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Str_Size

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Display the length of a string that the Cursor is in.
                  - A number preceded by \ (eg \123) is considered 1 char.
                  - A \ followed by a character is considered 1 char.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "None" "None"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : None

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Do Nothing. :-) Well actually this will force a refresh of the menu
              strip.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Set_Var" "Set_Var"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Set_Var

 PARAMETERS : VAR/A,VALUE,TOGGLE/S

 DESCRIPTION: Set an internal variable.

                VAR is the variable name and must be one of :
                  C_DIR
                  COMPILE
                  LINK
                  MAKE
                  EXECUTE
                  ERRORS
                  CLI
                  INSERT
                  INDENT
                  CAPTIVECRSR
                  MEMORY
                  BACKUPS
                  TABSIZE
                  AUTOTIME
                  MAXUNDO
                  RELOAD
                  PRINTER
                  SAVETABS
                  LOADTABS
                  TABSSPACES
                  SCRIPT

                VALUE is the value to set the variable to and may be :
                        a BOOLEAN -> TRUE/FALSE
                        a string  -> "fred"
                        a number  -> 123

                TOGGLE if present will toggle the value of a boolean variable

 See Also   : @{"Get_Var" Link "Get_Var"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Get_Var" "Get_Var"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Get_Var

 PARAMETERS : VAR/A

 DESCRIPTION: This command is for ARexx only and will retrieve the variable
              specified.
                VAR is the variable whose value you wish to retrieve and must be
                one of :
                         @{"C_DIR" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"COMPILE" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"LINK" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"MAKE" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"EXECUTE" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"ERRORS" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CLI" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"INSERT" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"INDENT" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CAPTIVECRSR" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"MEMORY" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"BACKUPS" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"TABSIZE" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"AUTOTIME" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"MAXUNDO" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"RELOAD" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"PRINTER" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"SAVETABS" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"LOADTABS" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"TABSSPACES" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"SCRIPT" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CurrX" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CurrY" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"LineNum" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"MaxLines" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"FileName" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"FilePath" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CurrLine" Link "Variables"}
                         @{"CurrWord" Link "Variables"}

 See Also   : @{"Set_Var" Link "Set_Var"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Variables" "Descriptions of Variables"
@TOC "MAIN"

        Descriptions of variables are :

C_DIR  <String>
  This string stores the directory to save the current buffer to when the
compile command is used.  Set this to "" if you want to save to the current
directory.

COMPILE <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the compile command. the 
C_DIR and the filename of the current buffer will be appended to this
string.

LINK <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the link command.

MAKE <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the Make command.

EXECUTE <String>
  This is the string that will be the default for the execute command.

ERRORS <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the Error command.

CLI <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the CLI command.

INSERT <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE for insert mode and FALSE for Overwrite mode.

INDENT <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE for Indent On and FALSE for No Indent.

CAPTIVECRSR <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE for a Captive Cursor and FALSE for a free
Cursor.

MEMORY <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE if SkoEd is to save all files loaded to a
Memory file on exit.

BACKUPS <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE is SkoEd is to rename the file being saved to
<File>.bak before saving.

TABSIZE <Integer>
  This variable is set to the number of spaces that a tab is defined as.

AUTOTIME <Integer>
  This variable is the number of minutes before the AutoSave command is
invoked.  Setting this value to 0 will turn off AutoSave.

MAXUNDO <Integer>
  This variable defines the maximum number of Undo commands that can be
performed.

RELOAD <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE if you want skoed to automatically invoke the
reload command upon startup.

PRINTER <String>
  This is the string that will be executed by the print commands.  A 
filename will be appended to this string.

SAVETABS <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE if you want leading spaces on a line to be 
converted to TABS when saving the file.

LOADTABS <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE wif you want TABS to be converted to SPACES
on loading a file.  FALSE will leave TABS alone.

TABSSPACES <Boolean>
  This variable is set to FALSE if you want to insert a TAB character into
your file.  TRUE will convert the TAB to upto TABSIZE spaces.

SCRIPT <Boolean>
  This variable is set to TRUE if the current file has the Script protection
bit set.  FALSE otherwise

CurrX <Integer> <Read Only>
  This is the column position of the cursor. Ranges from 1 to 4096.

CurrY <Integer> <Read Only>
  This is the abs position of the cursor relative to the Top most visible
line in the window.  Ranges from 1 to WindowSize.

LineNum <Integer> <Read Only>
  This is the current line number of the cursor.

MaxLines <Integer> <Read Only>
  This is the number of lines in the file.

FileName <String>
  This is the filename of the file.

FilePath <String>
  This is the filepath of the file.

CurrLine <String> <Read Only>
  This is the current line.

CurrWord <String> <Read Only>
  This is the word beneath the Cursor.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Buffer_Info" "Buffer_Info"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Buffer_Info

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Give some hopefully usefull information about the current buffer.
              Also allows you to :
                 convert the file from AMIGA -> IBM and back.
                 Set/Unset the Script bit.
                 Set/Unset the Read Only flag.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Set_Env" "Set_Env"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Set_Env

 PARAMETERS : STRING/F

 DESCRIPTION: Allow you to set a keymapping on the fly.
              Basically parses a given string or requests a string and parses
              it.  Parsing is done in the same manner as the Skoed.Config
              file is.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Set_Vars" "Set_Vars"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Set_Vars

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Allow you to set various variables via a requester.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Count_Braces" "Count_Braces"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Count_Braces

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Count all the { and } characters in the current buffer.

 See Also   : @{"Match" Link "Match"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Complete_Word" "Complete_Word"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Complete_Word

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Attempt to complete the word that was started.
              This will only work if the word has been used previously in the file.

 See Also   : @{"Word_Left" Link "Word_Left"} @{"Word_Right" Link "Word_Right"} @{"Word_End" Link "Word_End"} @{"Word_Delete" Link "Word_Delete"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Auto_Save" "Auto_Save"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Auto_Save

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Save the file that has had the most changes as <File>.Auto
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tab" "Tab"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Tab

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Insert/Overwrite with TABSIZE spaces.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Exit" "Exit"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Exit

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Exit SkoEd.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Iconify" "Iconify"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Iconify

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: Closes the SkoEd screen and window and open up a small window
              on WorkBench.  Use Right mouse button to UnIconify.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Reconfigure" "Reconfigure"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Reconfigure

 PARAMETERS : NONE

 DESCRIPTION: This removes all configuration details and reloads them from the
              SkoEd.Config ans SkoEd.Macro files.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Msg" "Msg"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : Msg

 PARAMETERS : MESSAGE/F

 DESCRIPTION: Puts the message given onto the message line.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ARexxCommand" "ARexx Command"
@TOC "MAIN"

COMMAND     : ARexx

 PARAMETERS : COMMAND/A

 DESCRIPTION: Execute an ARexx script given in COMMAND.
              Note: the script is executed Asynchronously.  SkoEd will continue to
              accept input from the user even if ARexx is giving commands.  However
              I believe under the current implementation if ARexx begins
              communicating with SkoEd then User commands are held until ARexx has
              finished but don't bet on it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EXAMPLES" "EXAMPLES"
@TOC "MAIN"


        @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Some Examples of configuring keys.@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

^Y = Del_Line; This will delete the current line.
CTRL Y=Del_Line;
    ^ Note the space

^Q = Exit; Exit Skoed
$F1 = "Hello"; Output the string "Hello" when Function key 1 is pressed.
&RETURN = Return; Make the enter key on the numeric keypad the same as Return key.
^UP = Page_Up;
$F5 = Zoom;
^$F5 = Explode;
^KB = Block_Begin;
!LP = Prev_Buffer;

Note that ^> is incorrect as the shift key needs to be down to get >.  You
should use ^#> or #^> or SHIFT CTRL >.

SkoEd sets the following keys automatically :

  RETURN = Return;
  &RETURN = Return;
  UP = Up;
  DOWN = Down;
  LEFT = Left;
  RIGHT = Right;
  DEL = Del;
  BACKSPACE = Backspace;
  TAB = Tab;

        Some examples of setting variables in Config files.

COMPILE = "cc";
CLI = "AShell";
MEMORY = FALSE;
BACKUPS = TRUE;
TABSIZE = 4;
MAXUNDO = 10;

        Have a look at the config and macro files given with this
distribution for more examples.  A lot of it is test configs that I use
so there is a fair range of key and variable configurations.

@ENDNODE

